# locator-mcp

MCP server that scans browser pages via Playwright/CDP and writes per-page locator registries.

## Layout

- `src/server.ts` — MCP tool definitions
- `src/scanner/` — page scan pipeline (discover → extract → generate → validate → save)
- `src/shared/` — registry I/O, constants, utilities
- `registry/` — local scan output (`{scanName}.json`); **never commit** JSON files
- `tests/` — Node test runner unit tests (`npm test`)

## Commands

- `npm run mcp` — run MCP server (`tsx src/server.ts`); used by `.cursor/mcp.json`
- `npm run dev` — same as `mcp`, for local terminal use
- `npm run build` — compile to `dist/` (`tsc`)
- `npm start` — run compiled server (`node dist/server.js`)
- `npm test` — unit tests

## MCP setup

Project config at `.cursor/mcp.json` uses `npm run mcp --prefix ${workspaceFolder}`. For global Cursor or Claude Desktop, use `npm run mcp --prefix <abs-path>` — see README.

## Git

Do not commit: `node_modules/`, `dist/`, `registry/*.json`, `.env*`.
Registry data is generated locally via `scan_page`.

## Token-efficient reads

Prefer `get_registry_keys` or `get_locator` over `get_registry` when working with large registries.
